<!-- FAQ -->
<div class="container sec" id="faq">
<div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:36px" class="reveal"><h2>Common Questions</h2></div>
<div class="faq-grid">
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>Why 15 stages instead of 3?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p>A 3-stage filter handles chlorine and basic sediment. But your water also carries chloramines (used in 30%+ of U.S. water systems), heavy metals from aging pipes, VOCs, and fluoride. Each stage group in the 5.0 targets a specific threat class that simpler filters let through.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>How often do I replace the filter?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p>Every <strong>6 months</strong> or 10,000 gallons — whichever comes first. Subscribe to save 15% with automatic delivery so you never have to think about it.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>Does the Vitamin C really do anything?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p>Yes — ascorbic acid directly neutralizes chlorine through a chemical reaction. It also provides topical antioxidant support. As estrogen declines, your body's internal antioxidant defense weakens. The 5.0 helps close that gap externally. Applied chemistry, not wellness marketing.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>Why 90 days instead of 30?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p>Hair grows at roughly 1 cm per month. One full growth mini-cycle takes 8–12 weeks. A 30-day guarantee means you'd decide before seeing hair results. We set 90 days because that's what the biology actually requires.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>Is NSF/ANSI 177 certification important?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p>Many filter brands make claims without third-party verification. NSF/ANSI 177 means the 5.0 has been independently tested and certified to remove 90%+ of chlorine for the full 10,000-gallon lifespan. Published performance data. Not our word — theirs.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>Should I get the 2.0 or 5.0?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p><strong>The 2.0 Handheld ($49)</strong> is ideal if your primary concern is chlorine. <strong>The 5.0 Stationary ($89)</strong> is for women who want maximum protection — catching chloramines, heavy metals, fluoride, and VOCs while adding vitamin infusion. If you're 45+ and experiencing hormonal changes, the 5.0's deeper filtration addresses more of what's actually in your water.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>Can I cancel the subscription anytime?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p>Yes — no contracts, no penalties, no "skip don't cancel" tricks. Cancel, pause, or adjust your schedule with one click. We earn your repeat business by being better, not by trapping you.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')"><button class="faq-btn"><span>Will it fit my shower?</span><span class="faq-ico">+</span></button><div class="faq-body"><p>The 5.0 fits any standard ½" shower arm — 99% of U.S. homes. Older or non-standard fixtures? We include a universal brass adapter. If it still doesn't fit, we'll send the right adapter free or give you a full refund.</p></div></div>
</div></div>


